BLINDING:  
 
The  order  of  the  within-participants  reward  conditions  and  the  between-participants  stimulus  set   
condition  will  be  randomly  determined  by  the  experimental  program  (see  cardsort.iqx).  
 
Experimenters  directly  involved  in  data  collection  will  be  unaware  of  the  order  condition,  and   
participants  will  be  unaware  of  the  alternative  order  condition.   Participants  will  experience  all   
conditions  of  the  within-participants  manipulations,  and  will  thus  be  aware  of  these   
manipulations,  but  will  be  blind  to  their  hypothesized  effects.   Experimenters  will  also  be  blind  to   
individual  participants’  scores  on  the  Stroop  executive  function  task  or  any  of  the  individual   
difference  questionnaires  administered  during  the  experimental  session.  
 
