DEVIATIONS  AND  OTHER  INFORMATION:  
 
The  primary  deviation  of  the  present  protocol  is  that  all  data  collection  will  be  conducted  online   
rather  than  in-person  due  to  COVID-19  protocols.   Every  effort  will  be  made  to  ensure  online   
participants  have  the  same  experience  as  in-person  participants  would.   Inquisit  Web  software   
( https://www.millisecond.com/products/inquisit6/weboverview.aspx )  will  be  used  to  ensure   
precision  millisecond  timing  is  still  possible  without  lag  from  internet  connections.   Participants   
recruited  from  prolific.co  will  also  be  informed  ahead  of  time  that  they  will  be  excluded  from  the 
study  and  risk  a  loss  of  compensation  by  the  terms  of  Prolific’s  data  quality  policy,  if  they  do  not   
attend  sufficiently  to  the  study.  
 
 
 
 
 
Another  deviation  is  that  the  Barratt  Impulsiveness  and  GAD  measures  will  not  be  administered   
as  they  were  in  the  original  study,  because  no  analyses  featuring  these  measures  were   
reported.   The  elimination  of  these  measures  is  also  unlikely  to  impact  this  replication  attempt.  
 
 
 
A  more  significant  change  to  the  original  protocol  is  that  following  the  practice  block  of  both  sets   
of  trials  in  the  task-switch  paradigm,  participants  will  complete  eight  items  directly  measuring   
their  anticipated  intrinsic  motivation  ( Deci  et  al.,  1994)  for  the  upcoming  task .   They  will  then   
proceed  to  the  main  task.   Although  this  has  more  potential  to  influence  the  results  of  the   
replication  attempt,  it  still  seems  unlikely  to  have  an  impact  because  similar  questions  were   
presented  in  close  proximity  to  the  task-switching  paradigm  in  the  original  study  when  the  Need   
for  Cognition  questionnaire  was  administered.   Furthermore,  the  potential  benefit  of  adding   
these  new  questions  is  that  they  may  represent  a  more  direct  measure  of  the  psychological   
construct  for  which  the  original  authors  were  using  the  Need  for  Cognition  questionnaire  as  a   
proxy.  
 
 
 
Still  another  deviation  for  the  original  study  is  instead  of  presenting  the  trials  of  the   
task-switching  paradigm  in  a  different  block-randomized  fashion  for  each  participant,  the  present   
protocol  will  create  a  single  block-randomized  order  of  140  trials  for  each  of  the  two  sets  of  trials   

and  then  present  this  same  order  to  all  participants.   This  is  unlikely  to  impact  this  replication   
attempt  and  may  again  represent  an  improvement  on  the  original  study  in  that  all  participants   
will  now  experience  the  exact  same  number  of  task-switch  and  task-repeat  trials  in  the  exact   
same  order.   This  change  will  also  facilitate  the  scoring  of  the  separate  accuracy  and  RT  indices   
for  each  type  of  trial  and  speed  the  analyses.  
 
 
 
Finally,  following  the  first  set  of  task-switching  task  trials,  participants  will  not  complete  the   
unspecified,  irrelevant  filler  task  featured  in  the  original  study.   They  will  also  have  an  8-minute   
music  break  featuring  a  selection  of  classical  pieces  by  Bach  ( rest_video.mp4 )  in  place  of  the   
8-minute  break  featuring  unspecified  music  in  the  original.   This  is  unlikely  to  impact  this   
replication  attempt.  
 
